1 6:36:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> No wonder when I do a /who Vera, I don't see ya around.  I have a ton of piercers.  I might have a piece of bloody leather or two.  I'll have to check.<br><br>Need any hammer handles?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Galen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/umallagarmisanthrope.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mallagar Misanthrope</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#993300>(11/27/01 7:04:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.zgeek.com/images/topics/skul1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> I'm not quite certain what you can use as a scout.<br><br>If you could give a short list of what you will be using I would be more than willing to help.<br><br>I.E. can you use chain? or just  leather and or studded?<br>Will you be using Piercers? (You have to don't you?)<br>And then any longbow would be nice right?<br><br>I'll probably be mucking about near the corwall hunters. If I get any drops from there I'll let ya know.<br><br>Meda <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uwinin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#993300>(11/27/01 7:11:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> I have a worn mithiran bow I picked up in the low level dungeon. It is collecting dust in my bank right now.<br><br>If scouts are anything like rangers, you'll be wanting to keep your gear at orange/yellow level if you solo. My ranger was dying to blues when he had blue gear, but can solo a yellow and two blues at once with orange/yellow gear. A nice bow and heavy damage arrows can drop a yellow in 2-3 shots (at level 11-12 at least). They are quite fun to play though.<br><br>I think I have a gyrgs cloak too. Quickness is important for lowering the time to aim and shoot.<br><br>--Winin <p>Winin the Sorcerer of Forgotten Grail Keepers(TM) on Guinevere<BR>Craewyn the Ranger of Dei Gratia on Palomides<BR>Winin the Bard of Shining Path on The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/umilossilvertune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milos Silvertune</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of Misfortune</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#993300>(11/27/01 7:30:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mdr-nhl.home.att.net/aruthsig.jpg HEIGHT=143 WIDTH=156></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> I have some Forester's Leggings you are welcome to have.<br><br>Edit: Also have some extra slashers and thrusters. <p><br><br><img src="http://mdr-nhl.home.att.net/sig3.jpg" border="0"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/umilossilvertune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milos Silvertune</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/27/01 7:30:57 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uwinin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#993300>(11/27/01 10:20:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> What level sorcerer are you now? I hardly see any sorcerers online, it makes me nervous about high level fun as a sorcerer. I need to go get out into the frontiers and do some RvR so I can see how it is as a sorc.<br><br>--Winin <p>Winin the Sorcerer of Forgotten Grail Keepers(TM) on Guinevere<BR>Craewyn the Ranger of Dei Gratia on Palomides<BR>Winin the Bard of Shining Path on The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ujaretfure.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaret Fure</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Mumbling Friar</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#993300>(11/27/01 10:28:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> Heya Veragon,<br><br>Aruth passed that staff to me, and I love it!  Thanks again!<br><br>I'm sure I have some stuff your scout could use in the bank.  I'll check what's there tonight.<br> <p>----------<br>Friar Jaret<br>God bless the <a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/bforgottengrailkeepers">Grail Keepers</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uveragon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veragon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>He of the Custom Title</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#993300>(11/30/01 2:51:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> Winin,<br><br>I am currently level 41, and enjoy the class still, but after playing Leala's scout in RVR last weekend I had so much fun I had to start my own ; ) I'm not giving up on the class, and will continue to play some time in the near future, but Exp for me now is at a standstill. I don't intend jumping back onto the levelling treadmill any time soon. I'm happy with my character as it is. I have the level 35 Body spec DD which is really nice btw, and I can still charm anything up to level 40 which is really all I could ask for. To progress my skills further or to gain any more spells I would like (45 body spec DD) I would have to get to level 47, which I don't want to do. It would take too much time and effort so I think I'll sit back and enjoy the game.<br><br>Hopefully with Sorcerers having access to bladeturn I may show my face from time to time, my goal is to get 10k realm points (8500atm) before striving to accomplish anything else. You'll enjoy the arsenal of spells available to Sorcerers in RVR as you increase in level. I found the AE root we have to be extremely reliable, and AE mez works great too, but unfortunately I don't have the Cloud of Senility spell, I only have Blanket which has a reduced radius, so I intend to start with the root because it has a faster cast time and larger radius followed by the mez. We took a group to one of the Midgard frontier zones last weekend and had a blast. I quite happily kept 20+ Midgards mezzed while the rest of the group mowed them down one by one. Mez is becoming an increasingly powerful spells in RVR warfare.<br><br>My scouts name is Yvi. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uveragon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veragon</A> at: 11/30/01 2:56:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uwinin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#993300>(11/30/01 6:49:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> Sounds like a good plan. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>I'm curious, at 41, how do you fare against the higher level folks in rvr? They claimed once that the difference, in rvr, between a level 40 and a level 50 was smaller than between 30 and 40, which was smaller than 20 and 30, etc. So that at the high end, character level was not as significant a factor as other things (like player skill). Do you find that to be true? <br><br>That was one of the things that drew me to the game since I'm not really a big fan of exp grinding and I really like pvp games.<br><br>--Winin<br><br>ps in half a bubble, I'll hit 27 and should be getting the aoe root. I can't wait. <p>Winin the Sorcerer of Forgotten Grail Keepers(TM) on Guinevere<BR>Craewyn the Ranger of Dei Gratia on Palomides<BR>Winin the Bard of Shining Path on The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uveragon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veragon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>He of the Custom Title</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#993300>(11/30/01 7:00:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> You are right about the variance in level as you get higher. The spell / skill system is a very good example of how the power of levels decreases as you get higher.<br><br>Between levels 1 and 10 you get spells upgraded almost every other level, if not every level. Between levels 11 and 20 you will gain maybe 1 spell every 3 to 4 levels. Then again from 21 to 30 you will gain maybe 1 spell every 5 levels. Between level 41 and 50 you can gain really only 1 spell per spell list, and it's that 1 spell that will determine, perhaps, your power over another. It's really not that big a difference really.<br><br>You will also notice the 'con' system as you increase in levels. An orange con at level 41 can be as high as level 49, making 50 a red con, whereas at level 10, an orange con can only be as high as level 12. This greatly effects your resists as well.<br><br>Like Mythic has said, upon reaching level 40, you should be aiming more towards getting items, or perhaps RVR warfare and just getting exp as it comes, rather than slogging it out to level 50.<br><br>I know at level 41 I would still stand toe to toe with a level 49 Hibernian enchanter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/uwinin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#993300>(11/30/01 12:02:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking For...</span><hr size=1> Ah, that is very good to hear. <br><br>Thanks,<br>--Winin <p>Winin the Sorcerer of Forgotten Grail Keepers(TM) on Guinevere<BR>Craewyn the Ranger of Dei Gratia on Palomides<BR>Winin the Bard of Shining Path on The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=36.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=36.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=36.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard